## Ignite

We are using Ignite team and must follow documentation and everytime search the web or Ignite Cookbook to understand how to implement one or another feature

## Do's and DONT's

- DO NOT write documentation or tests unless explicitly asked
- Do not create any examples of usage
- Do not ever try to run the project, it's user's duty
- Do not use default or fallback values, instead use guards to throw exception
- NEVER USE EMOJI
- Use web search and docs to understand which is the most proprietary modern implementation option
- Avoid any new file creations if possible only if asked or if it's really necessary

## Component styling

- You should never inline styles, but used Ignite themed() pattern

## Important to remember

- We are using yarn as our package manager
- Always look into ignite docs on the web https://github.com/infinitered/ignite/blob/master/docs/README.md to understand what is perfect implementation looking alike
- Use Ignite generators for components or screens
- We should always run lint fix for current file anf fix lint and type errors
- Always examine component of unnecessary effects usage and try to streamline it to avoid any unnecessary re-rendering

## Translating

- Remember that translation keys should be written using `:`
- We should not translate error text
- We should use native or custom tx property for components where it's presented
- We always should translate for en \ ru translations using internationalization rules
